From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: kernel-builder <builder@github.com>
Date: Fri, 6 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: change enum mmu_notifier_event to unsigned long

The mmu_notifier_range_init function was backported from a newer kernel
but the enum mmu_notifier_event type is not defined in kernel 4.19.
Since the event parameter is unused in the function body and enum values
are integer-compatible, use unsigned long instead to fix Clang compilation.

Signed-off-by: kernel-builder <builder@github.com>
---
 include/linux/mmu_notifier.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/include/linux/mmu_notifier.h b/include/linux/mmu_notifier.h
index 1b61c2a90..f8e1c3c45 100644
--- a/include/linux/mmu_notifier.h
+++ b/include/linux/mmu_notifier.h
@@ -343,7 +343,7 @@ static inline int mmu_notifier_clear_flush_young(struct mm_struct *mm)
 }
 
 static inline void mmu_notifier_range_init(struct mmu_notifier_range *range,
-					   enum mmu_notifier_event event,
+					   unsigned long event,
 					   unsigned flags,
 					   struct vm_area_struct *vma,
 					   struct mm_struct *mm,
